robyov]] {{flagicon|UKR}} (8).<br />\n'''Defenders:''' [[Vitali Litvinov]] (29 / 2), [[Vyacheslav Dayev]] (29 / 1), [[Alyaksandar Lukhvich]] {{flagicon|BLR}} (27 / 2), [[Andrei Malay]] (26), [[Marat Makhmutov]] (16), [[Andriy Sapuha]] {{flagicon|UKR}} (3), [[Sergei Burchenkov]] (3).<br />\n'''Midfielders:''' [[Andrei Gashkin]] (30 / 7), [[Vladimir Kazakov]] (28 / 2), [[Radaslaw Arlowski]] {{flagicon|BLR}} (22 / 3), [[Igor Semshov]] (18 / 1), [[Vladimir Leonchenko]] (14 / 1), [[Sergei Kormiltsev]] {{flagicon|UKR}} (12), [[Pavlo Shkapenko]] {{flagicon|UKR}} (10 / 1), [[Konstantin Zyryanov]] (5 / 3), [[Johann Duveau]] {{flagicon|FRA}} (4 / 1), [[Aleksandr Ignatyev]] (4).<br />\n'''Forwards:''' [[Dmitri Vyazmikin]] (27 / 8), [[Arsen Avakov (footballer)|Arsen Avakov]] {{flagicon|TJK}} (23 / 3), [[Rimantas \u017dvingilas]] {{flagicon|LTU}} (21 / 3), [[Valdas Trakys]] {{flagicon|LTU}} (21 / 2), [[Mihai Dr\u0103gu\u015f]] {{flagicon|ROM}} (7), [[Vyacheslav Kamoltsev]] (5), [[Maksim Aristarkhov]] (2 / 1).\n\nOne own goal scored by [[Aleksandr Cherkes]] ([[FC Fakel Voronezh]]).\n\n'''Manager:''' [[Vitaly Shevchenko]].\n\n'''Transferred out during the season:''' [[Mihai Dr\u0103gu\u015f]] {{flagicon|ROM}}, [[Aleksandr Ignatyev]], [[Andriy Sapuha]] {{flagicon|UKR}} (all to [[FC Lokomotiv Nizhny Novgorod]]).\n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[2000 in Russian football]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.rsssf.com/tablesr/rus00.html RSSSF]\n\n{{Russian Premier League seasons}}\n{{Football in Russia}}\n{{1999\u20132000 in European football (UEFA)}}\n{{2000\u201301 in European football (UEFA)}}\n\n[[Category:Russian Premier League seasons|2000]]\n[[Category:2000 in Russian football leagues|1]]\n[[Category:1999\u20132000 in European association football leagues|Russia]]\n[[Category:2000\u201301 in European association football leagues|Russia]]\n", "text_old": "[[FC Spartak Moscow|Spartak Moscow]] won their fifth consecutive [[Russian Premier League|Russian titl